      "content": "If receiving and picking logs are accurate, you should investigate issues within the storage and inventory management itself. Possible causes include misplacement during putaway, which the WMS doesn't register correctly, or minor damage that causes items to be written off without generating a corresponding transaction. Furthermore, potential environmental factors, like dust accumulation or mislabeling preventing accurate reading, could contribute to this chronic, small-scale variance.",
